00:32:53,475 --> 00:32:55,034
You're really her!

587
00:32:55,575 --> 00:32:57,734
How do you know I have a mole there?

588
00:32:57,925 --> 00:32:59,650
Of course I do!

589
00:33:00,525 --> 00:33:02,324
When you were born,

590
00:33:02,575 --> 00:33:04,175
I was still at home.

591
00:33:04,425 --> 00:33:05,500
I changed your diapers

592
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:07,375
every day.

593
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:09,679
Oh my,

594
00:33:10,175 --> 00:33:12,135
you're still alive!

595
00:33:13,399 --> 00:33:15,479
Thank heavens!

596
00:33:15,479 --> 00:33:17,640
God bless you!

597
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,425
Alright.

598
00:33:18,425 --> 00:33:19,704
Calm down.

599
00:33:19,704 --> 00:33:20,903
We can sit down and talk.

600
00:33:21,025 --> 00:33:22,250
Have a seat.

601
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,250
Sure. Thanks.

602
00:33:27,925 --> 00:33:28,646
Please.

603
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:31,650
Ma'am,

604
00:33:31,950 --> 00:33:32,910
just breathe.

605
00:33:32,910 --> 00:33:34,150
Take your time.

606
00:33:34,675 --> 00:33:36,600
Tell this young lady everything

607
00:33:36,975 --> 00:33:38,615
about her family.

608
00:33:39,025 --> 00:33:41,200
Your mother's name is Bai Yuzhen

609
00:33:41,625 --> 00:33:42,985
who married a Rong,

610
00:33:43,300 --> 00:33:45,040
Rong Dingkun,

611
00:33:45,075 --> 00:33:48,715
the only heir of
Mr. Rong's fourth son in Guojia Town.

612
00:33:49,550 --> 00:33:50,950
Granddaughters of the Rongs'

613
00:33:50,950 --> 00:33:52,275
all had a "Fang" in their names.

614
00:33:52,725 --> 00:33:54,884
You were the fourth of them all

615
00:33:54,925 --> 00:33:57,126
but the firstborn of your father,

616
00:33:57,425 --> 00:33:59,760
so your name was Fangzhen.

617
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:00,700
"Zhen" is the one with

618
00:34:01,025 --> 00:34:02,300
the character "Mu" (wood) on the side.

619
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:06,100
Fangzhen, call him Father.

620
00:34:07,075 --> 00:34:08,195
Father.

621
00:34:12,850 --> 00:34:14,650
What's your name, sweetie?

622
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:16,040
Do you remember?

623
00:34:16,040 --> 00:34:17,320
Fangzhen.

624
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:20,320
Fangzhen...

625
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:22,040
Your father left home

626
00:34:22,175 --> 00:34:23,816
to do business in Shanghai

627
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:26,919
before you were born.

628
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:29,560
He was too busy

629
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:31,800
to come back every year.

630
00:34:32,025 --> 00:34:33,785
When your mother was pregnant again,

631
00:34:34,050 --> 00:34:35,689
your grandmother gave her a hard time,

632
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:37,200
so she came back to live with us.

633
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,440
Later, she gave birth to your brother.

634
00:34:39,575 --> 00:34:41,725
Her husband was thrilled

635
00:34:41,975 --> 00:34:44,735
and sent back a message

636
00:34:44,825 --> 00:34:47,475
that he made a killing in Shanghai

637
00:34:47,525 --> 00:34:49,457
and he'd have you three over

638
00:34:49,457 --> 00:34:51,100
to live with him.

639
00:34:52,075 --> 00:34:55,120
At that time, I had moved to Guangzhou

640
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,159
with my husband.

641
00:34:56,650 --> 00:34:58,611
Your mother was so excited

642
00:34:58,611 --> 00:34:59,900
and shared the news with me in a letter.

643
00:35:00,825 --> 00:35:02,345
My poor sister!

644
00:35:03,775 --> 00:35:05,495
She died of illness

645
00:35:05,495 --> 00:35:07,735
on the way to Shanghai

646
00:35:08,150 --> 00:35:09,700
with you and your brother.

647
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,840
I heard

648
00:35:12,925 --> 00:35:15,246
when her husband came back to bury you,

649
00:35:15,246 --> 00:35:17,766
he carried the virus
to the Rongs by accident

650
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:21,100
which killed them all.

651
00:35:22,225 --> 00:35:24,906
That was a heavy blow to him.

652
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:27,625
He sold all their property there

653
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:28,800
and returned to Shanghai

654
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,159
without coming back again.

655
00:35:30,550 --> 00:35:31,511
Fangzhen,

656
00:35:32,159 --> 00:35:33,199
how...

657
00:35:33,575 --> 00:35:36,050
How did you survive?

658
00:35:36,725 --> 00:35:39,124
Have you reunited with your father?

659
00:35:39,475 --> 00:35:40,874
Where's your brother?

660
00:35:42,525 --> 00:35:43,924
We got separated.

661
00:35:45,575 --> 00:35:47,615
My mother didn't die of illness.

662
00:35:49,100 --> 00:35:52,660
She was killed

663
00:35:54,425 --> 00:35:55,705
by someone halfway.

664
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:57,919
How come?

665
00:35:58,825 --> 00:36:00,386
I was too young

666
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:03,065
to get a good look at the killer's face.

667
00:36:04,175 --> 00:36:06,275
He stabbed me

668
00:36:06,950 --> 00:36:08,750
and I fell into the water

669
00:36:09,650 --> 00:36:10,930
and floated

670
00:36:11,350 --> 00:36:12,909
downstream

671
00:36:14,025 --> 00:36:15,775
until my foster parents found me.

672
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:20,280
They followed the trace

673
00:36:20,475 --> 00:36:22,516
to look for my mother and brother.

674
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:26,370
But by the time they got there,

675
00:36:29,525 --> 00:36:31,006
all they saw

676
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:32,975
was her body.

677
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:36,521
There was no sign of my brother.

678
00:36:37,350 --> 00:36:38,551
It was them

679
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,561
who paid for

680
00:36:41,325 --> 00:36:42,725
her funeral.

681
00:36:43,275 --> 00:36:44,560
So,

682
00:36:45,919 --> 00:36:48,520
you have her ashes?

683
00:36:48,675 --> 00:36:49,679
But...

684
00:36:49,679 --> 00:36:51,599
But the neighbors said

685
00:36:51,599 --> 00:36:53,925
your father buried all your ashes

686
00:36:54,175 --> 00:36:57,335
into the family graveyard.

687
00:37:01,050 --> 00:37:02,850
They could be someone else's.

688
00:37:08,625 --> 00:37:09,475
Aunt,

689
00:37:10,150 --> 00:37:11,959
is this your photo?

690
00:37:13,150 --> 00:37:14,040
Yes,

691
00:37:15,025 --> 00:37:16,344
but the Rongs

692
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:19,080
grabbed the original one.

693
00:37:24,725 --> 00:37:26,644
Can you tell me more about my father?

694
00:37:27,575 --> 00:37:29,055
What kind of person he was?

695
00:37:35,075 --> 00:37:36,915
He was a good man.

696
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:38,920
Everyone in the village said

697
00:37:39,175 --> 00:37:40,655
your mother got lucky.

698
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:42,861
He was good-looking,

699
00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:45,101
reliable and rich.

700
00:37:45,250 --> 00:37:47,371
He never talked to

701
00:37:47,475 --> 00:37:50,475
other women,

702
00:37:50,725 --> 00:37:52,485
but worked really hard.

703
00:37:52,925 --> 00:37:55,246
Seeing that the land was low-yield,

704
00:37:55,275 --> 00:37:57,194
he went to work for others

705
00:37:57,375 --> 00:37:59,294
and started his own business

706
00:37:59,350 --> 00:38:01,325
from scratch.

707
00:38:01,550 --> 00:38:03,870
He was a good husband and father, too,

708
00:38:04,450 --> 00:38:06,810
who had people bring back

709
00:38:07,399 --> 00:38:09,760
foreign perfume,

710
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:12,841
lipsticks and fabrics.

711
00:38:13,399 --> 00:38:15,639
He loved you all.

712
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:18,280
After his business took off,

713
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:21,159
he rebuilt the Rongs' ancestral hall.

714
00:38:21,375 --> 00:38:23,159
Whenever your grandmother
talked about him,

715
00:38:23,199 --> 00:38:24,439
she'd tell everyone

716
00:38:24,525 --> 00:38:27,400
what a lucky star Ho was

717
00:38:27,525 --> 00:38:29,846
and he was bound to succeed.

718
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:33,560
Then his business did
grow bigger and bigger.

719
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:35,360
Your grandmother

720
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:36,680
was right.

721
00:38:36,975 --> 00:38:38,336
Unfortunately,

722
00:38:38,500 --> 00:38:40,540
she didn't get to see that.

723
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:42,600
Who's "Ho"?

724
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:44,110
That's your father.

725
00:38:44,325 --> 00:38:46,045
"Ho" is his pet name.

726
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:48,320
"Ho"?

727
00:38:51,275 --> 00:38:53,075
That name sounds familiar.

728
00:38:54,375 --> 00:38:55,415
"Ho"...

729
00:38:59,550 --> 00:39:00,390
Relax.

730
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:02,439
Don't push yourself

731
00:39:02,439 --> 00:39:03,300
too hard.

732
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:04,381
One step at a time.

733
00:39:05,175 --> 00:39:05,935
Ma'am,

734
00:39:06,075 --> 00:39:06,835
how about this?

735
00:39:07,025 --> 00:39:08,105
You can stay here

736
00:39:08,375 --> 00:39:09,454
these days.

737
00:39:09,550 --> 00:39:10,765
Let us know

738
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:11,846
if you think of anything else.

739
00:39:11,846 --> 00:39:12,565
Alright?

740
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:14,840
Sure.

741
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,040
I will.

742
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:16,919
No problem.

743
00:39:16,919 --> 00:39:17,639
Wen,

744
00:39:17,679 --> 00:39:19,050
lead her to the room.

745
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,080
You can go with him.

746
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,040
Thanks.

747
00:39:43,575 --> 00:39:44,439
Mr. Jiashang,

748
00:39:46,875 --> 00:39:49,236
your father was craving opium

749
00:39:49,236 --> 00:39:51,199
and almost trashed the room.

750
00:39:51,199 --> 00:39:53,650
Your sister put the prescribed drugs

751
00:39:53,650 --> 00:39:55,450
into his water and fed it to him

752
00:39:55,825 --> 00:39:56,944
which put him to sleep.

753
00:39:57,425 --> 00:39:58,344
You may leave.

754
00:39:58,425 --> 00:39:59,266
Yes.

755
00:40:22,625 --> 00:40:23,439
Father,

756
00:40:24,375 --> 00:40:25,325
how do you feel?

757
00:40:25,325 --> 00:40:26,325
What would you like to eat?

758
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:27,959
Go away.

759
00:40:28,225 --> 00:40:29,625
I called Dr. Robert

760
00:40:29,625 --> 00:40:30,504
in America.

761
00:40:31,350 --> 00:40:32,951
He's interested in your case.

762
00:40:33,425 --> 00:40:34,466
I'll escort you to New York

763
00:40:34,466 --> 00:40:36,025
if you want to go.

764
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:37,899
I can have your wife

765
00:40:37,899 --> 00:40:38,875
or any concubine you like

766
00:40:38,875 --> 00:40:39,954
keep you company.

767
00:40:40,250 --> 00:40:41,600
If the operation goes well,

768
00:40:42,325 --> 00:40:44,246
you'll be able to walk Fanghua

769
00:40:44,725 --> 00:40:46,005
down the aisle at her wedding.

770
00:40:52,159 --> 00:40:53,300
Jiashang,

771
00:40:53,650 --> 00:40:55,900
you know what the biggest irony is?

772
00:40:57,625 --> 00:40:59,120
You didn't want to

773
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:01,840
take over our family business at first.

774
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:03,639
Now that I have,

775
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:06,380
I'll do what needs to be done.

776
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:07,980
By that,

777
00:41:09,479 --> 00:41:10,550
you mean to destroy

778
00:41:10,550 --> 00:41:14,150
this family?

779
00:41:21,025 --> 00:41:22,144
It's the opposite.

780
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:24,600
I'm trying to save it.

781
00:41:26,575 --> 00:41:27,399
Father,

782
00:41:28,475 --> 00:41:30,475
you established this empire,

783
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:32,800
but it doesn't belong to you alone.

784
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:35,424
The shareholders and co-founders

785
00:41:35,750 --> 00:41:37,525
won't allow you
to ruin everything we have

786
00:41:37,525 --> 00:41:39,040
for your personal grudge
against Meng Xu'an.

787
00:41:39,625 --> 00:41:41,504
Neither will I allow you

788
00:41:41,550 --> 00:41:42,800
to ruin my brother and sisters' future

789
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,239
for your own agenda.

790
00:41:46,100 --> 00:41:46,780
Father,

791
00:41:47,825 --> 00:41:49,866
when you start to do more

792
00:41:50,150 --> 00:41:51,325
for others

793
00:41:51,325 --> 00:41:52,825
and our family than yourself,

794
00:41:52,950 --> 00:41:54,719
you can judge me.

795
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,560
Without me,

796
00:41:58,950 --> 00:42:01,510
you wouldn't have anything.

797
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:05,101
I've done so much for this family,

798
00:42:07,075 --> 00:42:08,595
for you all.

799
00:42:09,975 --> 00:42:12,894
Do you know what all that cost me?

800
00:42:13,625 --> 00:42:14,466
What about you?

801
00:42:15,550 --> 00:42:18,310
What have you done for us?

802
00:42:18,875 --> 00:42:20,716
You don't get to judge me

803
00:42:20,716 --> 00:42:23,355
or call me selfish!

804
00:42:24,225 --> 00:42:25,425
You do everything

805
00:42:25,775 --> 00:42:27,094
for yourself.

806
00:42:27,375 --> 00:42:29,295
To you, women are toys.

807
00:42:29,295 --> 00:42:30,400
Children can be traded

808
00:42:30,656 --> 00:42:32,136
for marriage alliance.

809
00:42:32,850 --> 00:42:33,850
After you woke up

810
00:42:33,850 --> 00:42:35,100
and heard what happened to Fanghua,

811
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:36,820
you kept calling her cheap.

812
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:38,871
Then when Wu Yunchi agreed to marry her,

813
00:42:39,075 --> 00:42:40,434
you called her a good girl.

814
00:42:42,275 --> 00:42:43,159
Father,

815
00:42:44,025 --> 00:42:45,520
do you have any idea

816
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:46,625
how much you've hurt

817
00:42:46,625 --> 00:42:47,675
Fanghua and Fanglin?

818
00:42:51,425 --> 00:42:53,386
What's the point of

819
00:42:54,199 --> 00:42:56,000
raising those girls

820
00:42:56,479 --> 00:42:59,040
if they can't marry people I need?

821
00:43:04,900 --> 00:43:09,220
♪The aftertaste of love lingers♪

822
00:43:12,780 --> 00:43:16,540
♪Hatred snaps roses in two♪

823
00:43:19,620 --> 00:43:26,100
♪Tear-like drizzle seems fine♪

824
00:43:26,820 --> 00:43:32,620
♪Where's the key to one's heart♪

825
00:43:39,780 --> 00:43:43,700
♪Who knows what lies ahead♪

826
00:43:47,700 --> 00:43:51,300
♪The moon isn't lonelier than us♪

827
00:43:54,220 --> 00:43:59,620
♪Sitting alone to see
begonias in the breeze♪

828
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:08,340
♪I still remember our dance♪

829
00:44:08,620 --> 00:44:14,900
♪I remember the way you looked at me♪

830
00:44:16,420 --> 00:44:22,940
♪The autumn wind can't
whisk away thick leaves♪

831
00:44:24,220 --> 00:44:27,140
♪However time streams♪

832
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:30,500
♪Hearts remain tiny cities♪

833
00:44:30,660 --> 00:44:36,300
♪If we could be together in this life♪

834
00:44:39,660 --> 00:44:46,140
♪I remember the way you smiled at me♪

835
00:44:47,420 --> 00:44:53,860
♪The autumn wind can't
whisk away innocent leaves♪

836
00:44:55,100 --> 00:44:58,100
♪However time streams♪

837
00:44:58,100 --> 00:45:01,500
♪Hearts remain tiny cities♪

838
00:45:01,900 --> 00:45:07,140
♪If we could be together in this life♪

839
00:45:07,580 --> 00:45:12,900
♪And trust each other completely♪

840
00:45:13,500 --> 00:45:18,220
♪However time flies♪

841
00:45:19,300 --> 00:45:24,860
♪We're destined to love♪

842
00:45:27,380 --> 00:45:29,940
♪And cherish each other♪

